This runtime installs a conda environment from a stamped lockfile.

After bootstrap, commands are passed through to the configured delegate executable.

Usage: cs-template [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  bootstrap  Bootstrap the selected runtime packages into the install path
  status     Print runtime status (install path, channels, packages)
  shell      Activate an environment via subshell (alias for conda spawn)
  uninstall  Uninstall this runtime: remove the install path and environments
  help       Show this help message

Options:
  -V, --version
          Show the runtime version

  -v, --verbose
          Increase output detail

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress non-essential output

      --path <PATH>
          Runtime install path to use instead of the stamped default

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Quick start:

  cs-template bootstrap                           Install conda into ~/.conda/cs-template
  cs-template create -n myenv python=3.12 numpy   Create an environment
  cs-template shell myenv                         Activate (spawns a subshell)
  exit                                   Leave the environment

Management:

  cs-template status                              Show installation details
  cs-template uninstall                           Remove the install path and environments

Pass-through:

  Any command not listed above is passed through to conda:
  cs-template install, cs-template remove, cs-template list, cs-template env, cs-template info, cs-template config, ...

Docs: https://jezdez.github.io/conda-ship/
